<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn403">  403  This &lsquo;second Adam&rsquo; (so-called by Joyce in conversation with Jacques Mercanton) is no other than Carolus Linnaeus, the great Swedish botanist and taxonomist. He invented the modern system of nomenclature in the life sciences. Many of the terms used in this passage derive from his work on the sexual system of the plants; see John O'Hanlon, &lsquo;In the Language of Flowers,&rsquo; <cite>A Wake Newslitter</cite> 16 (February 1979) 9-12.  </div>
